Basic GeneOntology plugin to create GO pathways visualizing all genes annotated with a specific term or its one of its subterms. The terms are structured hierarchically. All genes are annotated and data can be automatically visualized on them.
Basic GO plugin to visualized genes annotated with a specific GO term.
This plugin has two main function: (1) Exports a pathway as an html page. (2) Export pathway statistics result with all pathway images as html pages.
Exports pathways and pathway statistics results as HTML pages.

This plugin implements a standard Gene Set Enrichment Analysis method that can be used to identify over represented pathways in the data set.
It also allows to load gene sets from MSigDB (http://www.broadinstitute.org/gsea/).
Gene set enrichment analysis plugin for PathVisio
Library containing gene set enrichment algorithm used by GSEA plugin.

The MAPPBuilder plugin helps you get started quickly on creating a new pathway. Given a list of gene identifiers, MAPPBuilder will build a simple prototype pathway for you containing those genes, eliminating the step of manual searching for each gene/gene product you want to include.
Automated way to create data nodes from file.
This plugin adds a sidetab in PathVisio, containing a mini map view of the pathway. With the red rectangle the user can navigate through larger pathways.
A mini map view of the pathways that allows easy navigation in larger pathways.
PathVisioRPC is an XML-RPC interface for PathVisio. It allows users to use PathVisio functionality directly in their favourite analytical environment,
PathVisioRPC is an XML-RPC interface for PathVisio.

The BridgeDb configuration plugin let's you configure identifier mapping resources to be used in PathVisio. The mapping resources will be used to link pathway identifiers to identifiers in your dataset, during data import and visualization. The mapping resources are also used to fetch information for the backpage side-panel.
The BridgeDb configuration plugin let's you configure identifier mapping resources to be used in PathVisio.
The Quick Search plug-in adds a search box to the main toolbar of PathVisio. With this search box you can search for identifiers and text within the pathway that is currently open.
The Quick Search plug-in adds a search box with which one can search for identifiers and text within the pathway that is currently open.
This plugin allows users to create pathway diagrams in the Systems Biology Graphical Notation (SBGN). A description of this standard notation can be found here: http://www.sbgn.org/Main_Page.
Draw diagrams with the Systems Biology Graphical Notation (SBGN)
This plugin allows users to export and import pathways in BioPAX format. The plugin support BioPAX level 3. The import functionality is limited (pathways might need manual rearranging of objects).
Import and export pathways in BioPAX level 3.

This plugin connects to the online pathway databases, WikiPathways, and allows users to search and browse pathways from PathVisio directly. It also enables updating and upload functionality (special permissions are required which can be requested from the WP developers).
Browse, search and update pathways from WikiPathways
This plugins allows the conversion of pathway elements into other types, e.g. a Label into a Metabolite or an Interaction into a GraphicalLine.
Convert a pathway element into another type, e.g. Label into Metabolite.

NIMWiz provides assistance in importing metabolomics data into PathVisio.It works with any data table with one column containing the names of metabolites. Nimwiz adds an extra column to that table containing identifiers from e.g. HMDB or ChEBI.Lookup is automatic where possible and manual where necessary. The assistance of the plugin greatly accelerates the lookup process.If there is an exact match in the dictionary, Nimwiz performs the lookup automatically. For near matches, Nimwiz lets you manually pick the best match from a list.
NIMWiz assists looking up identifiers for named metabolites/genes

The PathSBML plugin allows researchers to visualize and overlay data on the same pathway models they use in simulation experiments. Exporting these models as GPML would also allow them to be uploaded to Wikipathways for community curation.
The PathSBML plugin allows researchers to visualize and overlay data on the same pathway models they use in simulation experiments.
Plugin to visualize data on Interactions.
Plugin to visualize data on Interactions.
Module to register info providers for different data node types, like BiomartConnect for gene products, MetInfo for metabolites,...

Plugin connects to Biomart to retrieve additional information about GeneProdcuts. The plugin currently implements three different Information Providers: BasicProvider, VariationProvider and SequenceProvider.
Plugin connects to Biomart to retrieve additional information about GeneProdcuts.
ComplexViz is a PathVisio Plugin. It has been developed specially for simplifying visualization of data on the many complexes of Reactome pathways.
Plugin enables visualization of complex component node data on the parent complex.
RegInt is a plugin that allows users to visualize regulatory interactions in the side panel of PathVisio
Visualize regulatory interactions in the side panel of PathVisio

Query the Rhea webservice using the ChEBI/UniProt IDs or text labels of the two nodes the interaction connects to find identifiers. Automatically annotate the interaction with the selected identifier.
The FYI (FindYourInteractions) plugin suggests suitable identifiers for the interactions by querying
The TissueAnalyzer plugin for PathVisio provides a simple three step workflow for users to load, analyze and visualize tissue-specific pathway activity.
Importing baseline expression data from Expression Atlas
